{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Developing a single unified model that could perform competently in all three would hail an important breakthrough.",
    "In order to perform this, a model would have to have a common intermediary space for which it could map between the text and image spaces.",
    "We posit that this space would most likely be graph-based due to their expressive nature.",
    "However, a textual representation may also be performant as Gao et al. [130] showed reasoning in the text space improved performance over graph-based reasoning in VQA.In summary, Vision-Language tasks such as those discussed in this paper are set to have a fruitful future, with many opportunities for various graph structures to be exploited.",
